    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="1011"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1011">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.01/98: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 1, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>544. I will send my recommendations later on today regarding the general question
                    of recognition of the new government. However, prior to any determination I
                    would appreciate the Department’s immediate instructions whether I should
                    establish an informal contact either with the Minister for Foreign Affairs<note
                        n="11" xml:id="d1011fn11">Camilo Ponce Enríquez.</note> or with Velasco
                    Ibarra or whether, in case they desire to see me, I should go.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
